.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS.CONCEALEDSAMPLES" "3JS" "August 15, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats.concealedSamples \- RTCInboundRtpStreamStats:
concealedSamples property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]concealedSamples\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[R] dictionary indicates the total
number of concealed samples for the received audio track over the
lifetime of this stats object.
.PP
A concealed sample is a sample that was lost or arrived too late to be
played out, and therefore had to be replaced with a locally generated
synthesized sample.
Note that lost samples are reported in \f[CR]packetsLost\f[R], while
late packets are reported in \f[CR]fecPacketsDiscarded\f[R].
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The value is undefined for video streams.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A positive integer.
.SH SEE ALSO
